5 Subject: Motor vehicles; use of required lamps; use of required lights;
6 windshield wipers
7 Statement of purpose of bill as introduced: This bill proposes to require
8 operators of vehicles on a highway to illuminate required lamps while
9 windshield wipers are in continuous use or as a result of weather conditions
10 that limit visibility and to require that a motor vehicle’s taillights be visible
11 from a distance of at least 300 feet behind the vehicle.
12 An act relating to use of illuminating lights and visibility of taillights
13 It is hereby enacted by the General Assembly of the State of Vermont:
14 Sec. 1. 23 V.S.A. § 1243(b) is amended to read:
15 (b) Every A person operating a vehicle upon a highway within this State,
16 shall illuminate all front, tail or rear, and clearance lamps with which the
17 vehicle is required to be equipped pursuant to this chapter at any time all of the
18 following times:
19 (1) from From 30 minutes after sunset to 30 minutes before sunrise and
20 at any other time when.
